The Chief Executive Officer of Labo Entertainment, Olabisi Akanbi, has said he is on a quest to raise as many stars as possible in the entertainment industry. Akanbi, who recently bagged a Doctorate degree in Property Management and Estate Development from the European American University (Ghana), also stated that through his foundation, he would continue to empower other youths, even outside the entertainment industry. Speaking at the event, he said, “This is a very positive movement in my career. I am sure this would position me for another successful direction and I am already preparing for the task ahead. I believe firmly that education is the best legacy. Through Labo Foundation, we would also support students in realising their dreams by educating them and help their educational dream. This will prepare them to become great model in the future. “I always say that I am on a mission to raise more stars in the entertainment industry and give them a platform to showcase their talents to the world.” Meanwhile, rising singer, Oladotun Alade, aka Dotman, who is signed to Labo Entertainment congratulated his label boss for the achievement. He said, “I am very happy to see my boss achieving a lot. “Being conferred with a doctor of science degree is a big achievement. I wish him more success.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com